<br>
All other differences aside, this makes them hit closer to their damage cap than an equally specced Skald. <br>
<br>
I actually think Mythic was onto something here in boosting a melee hybrid Weaponskill to higher than rogues but still lower than a pure melee.<br>
<br>
If we can get the same done to the Mid melee hybrids, we would not be the rogue fodder than we are now while regaining equality with Hib melee hybrids and getting closer to being competitive with the full tanks with improvements to out other abilities as well.<br>
<br>
Any comments? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=t0a5t>t0a5t</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/18/03 10:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=581.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Could Skalds use a Weaponskill boost like Champs got?</span><hr size=1> And it wasn't just Champs that got help..<br>
<br>
Quoting from 1.47 patch notes:<br>
<br>
&quot; - Paladins now have increased hit points.<br>
<br>
- Champions have had their hit points and melee damages increased. &quot;<br>
<br>
Umm Champs got a boost to hitpoints AND melee damage.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 273<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/18/03 11:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=581.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Could Skalds use a Weaponskill boost like Champs got?</span><hr size=1> Champs don't have much higher (if higher at all) weaponskill than us. I thnk before that patch their weaponskill was set too low.<br>
 <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kortzdymundskyn>Kortz Dymundskyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/18/03 12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=581.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Could Skalds use a Weaponskill boost like Champs got?</span><hr size=1> Actually, Im afraid to say that Champs do have a slightly higher skill than Skalds do.<br>
<br>
After looking at an equally compared (Same skill spec, same stats, same level), the Champ came out with about a 10 point increase in melee ability.<br>
<br>
Level comparison was made with a 20 Skald and 20 Champ, no buffs, no magic. Straight numbers.<br>
<br>
But I dont think 10 points is enough to really expect an increase in melee for us.... <p>Bays Endruhms<br>
